  "body": "I happened to notice that React will throw `Hooks can only be called inside the body of a function component` if a sibling element calls `ReactDOMServer.renderToStaticMarkup`. I have a [fiddle](https://jsfiddle.net/er4kL3of/) that shows this behavior (I think you need to manually open your console to see the error).\r\n\r\nIf you wrap the sibling element in a component or even just assign it a variable, this issue does not occur.\r\n\r\nIt's easy to get around and is a pretty specific bug, but why might this be happening?\r\n\r\n",
